headlines.description: — Malik Beasley scored 26 points, Cade Cunningham had 21 points and 11 assists and the Detroit Pistons beat the Boston Celtics 117-97 on Wednesday night in a matchup of two of the NBA's hottest teams.
headlines.shortLinkText: Malik Beasley scores 26 points to help the streaking Pistons rout the Celtics, 117-97

headlines.description: — Tyrese Haliburton had 33 points and 11 assists to help the Indiana Pacers beat the Toronto Raptors 111-91 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Tyrese Haliburton has 33 points and 11 assists in the Pacers' 111-91 victory over the Raptors

headlines.description: — Jalen Brunson had 34 points and seven assists, Mikal Bridges scored 28 points and the New York Knicks held off the Philadelphia 76ers 110-105 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Brunson and Bridges help Knicks hold off 76ers 110-105 and send Philly to its 9th straight loss

events.name: Portland Trail Blazers at Washington Wizards

headlines.description: — Shaedon Sharpe threw down a vicious one-handed slam that was immediately hailed as one of the best dunks of the season, part of a career-best 36-point performance that carried the...
headlines.shortLinkText: Shaedon Sharpe's eye-popping dunk caps a career night as the Trail Blazers beat the Wizards 129-121

events.name: Oklahoma City Thunder at Brooklyn Nets

headlines.description: — Shai Gilgeous-Alexander scored 27 points, Chet Holmgren had 22 points and 17 rebounds, and the Oklahoma City Thunder rebounded from a stunning collapse with a game-changing blitz in the fourth quarter to beat the Brooklyn Nets 129-121 on Wednesday...
headlines.shortLinkText: Thunder bounce back from stunning collapse with fourth-quarter blitz to beat the Nets 129-121

headlines.description: — Tyler Herro scored 24 points and added 10 assists, Duncan Robinson scored 24 points off the bench and the Miami Heat shot a season-best 59% in a 131-109 win over the Atlanta Hawks on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Herro, Robinson each score 24, and the Heat hit 23 3s on the way to 131-109 win over Hawks

headlines.description: — James Harden made seven 3-pointers and scored 30 points, and the Los Angeles Clippers beat the Chicago Bulls 122-117 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: James Harden scores 30, Clippers hold off Bulls 122-117 to stop 3-game skid

headlines.description: — Keegan Murray scored a season-high 26 points and Zach LaVine added 22 to lift the hot-shooting Sacramento Kings to a 118-101 win over the Utah Jazz on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Murray scores 26 points to spark hot-shooting Kings to a 118-101 win over Jazz

events.name: San Antonio Spurs at Houston Rockets

headlines.description: — Amen Thompson had 25 points and eight rebounds, Jalen Green added 21 points and seven rebounds and the Houston Rockets beat the San Antonio Spurs 118-106 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Amen Thompson scores 25 points in the Rockets' 118-106 victory over the Spurs
